entry.title: Avoid exposing files in TabStateFileManager
entry.content:
This CL refactors TabStateFileManager so TabState filenames

are not exposed (except if the TabState files are read directly

from the TabState directory). This is to make way for migrating

the TabState schema to FlatBuffers. We need to be able to have

a FlatBuffer TabState file and regular TabState file sitting

side by side in the TabState directory and exposing TabState

file names significantly complicates this. From my study of the

codebase, it appears we don't need to expose TabState files

but rather passing identifiers (id and isEncrypted) to find the corresponding TabState file to save or delete will suffice.

entry.title: [ios] Fix SerializeWebStateList to keep items with pending navigations
entry.content:
SerializeWebStateList had a bug where the items with pending items but

no navigation items. It had no visible impact because the session will

be saved again when the item navigation commits.



However, with the new session serialization logic, the WebStateList

state is not considered dirty if the only change is a navigation that

commit. This could results in data loss because in that case the list

will not reference this item.



Fix GetIndexOfWebStatesToDrop() to consider that WebState with a load

pending are not dropped (they may still be dropped on load if the app

could not save the session after the navigation commit, e.g. in case

of a crash).



Update the unit test to check that those tabs are not dropped.

compositionend event's `data` field is populated with all the

characters from the start of the composition through the end of the

text.

index, of the desired substring.

entry.title: CCA: Fix race condition if CCA fails to load document scanner
entry.content:
If CCA fails to load document scanner, there might be a race condition

between OnMojoDisconnected and LoadDocumentScannerInternal. If

LoadDocumentScannerInternal is executed before OnMojoDisconnected, the

remote will be bound while it is already bound.



This CL enhances

1. Use a new flag to avoid such race condition.

2. If get LoadModelResult!=OK, don't do redundant retry.

entry.title: The font-variant shorthand is incorrectly serialized for none.

Font-variant: none should return 'none,' but Blink spelled out its

longhand properties. Besides, it serialized longhands where

entry.title: Sync: Simplify ProtocolTypes() and EncryptableUserTypes()
entry.content:
The concept of "protocol types" existed to distinguish from "proxy

types", which didn't have a protocol representation.

As of crrev.com/c/4922312, the concept of proxy types doesn't exist

anymore, so "protocol types" is now the same as "all types", so no more

need to explicitly list all the types.



There's one minor behavior difference: Previously, ProtocolTypes()

didn't include ModelType::SEGMENTATION, which was an oversight. (This

ModelType is partially implemented, but not actually used yet.)



Additionally and similarly, this CL also slightly simplifies

EncryptableUserTypes(): Now there's no more need to drop

non-protocol types, because they don't exist.

entry.title: Reland: Recalculate style before setting ICB size for printing.
entry.content:
One change, compared to the initial attempt: Set zero page margins in

the browser test, to avoid crbug.com/1491775



Original commit comment follows:



A zoom factor used when viewing a webpage on screen may have been set in

computed style. This would affect @page margin resolution incorrectly

when entering print mode, which in turn would result in an incorrect

initial containing block size. To fix this, recalculate style before

calculating the page area size.



Since we now recalculate style before setting any initial containing

block size for printing at all, viewport units will not be resolved

correctly. So make sure that they get calculated before laying out. This

used to be triggered by calling LayoutViewportWasResized(). It turns out

though, now that we need to do this unconditionally before the first

layout, that LayoutViewportWasResized() does more than we want. For

printing, we don't need to re-evaluate media queries, and we do not want

a resize event to be fired. Therefore, split the viewport units dirtying

into a separate function. Introduce a lambda in

ForceLayoutForPagination() to avoid repetitive code.



Make PrintBrowserTest.NoResizeEvent more evil, by modifying its resource

HTML file to use a named page, and also a wide DIV. This would make the

test fail without this CL.



Add external/wpt/css/printing/ to the scalefactor200 virtual test suite.

Three other tests (the already existing page-margin-xxx tests) would

also fail without this fix, but add a test for this specific issue

(abspos) as well.

entry.title: Support mask-clip values: <geometry-box> and no-clip
entry.content:
This patch wires up and implements the specified behavior for

and no-clip values on the mask-clip property, which is

behind the CSSMaskingInterop flag.



Spec: https://drafts.fxtf.org/css-masking/#the-mask-clip



With this patch, we now support the following on boxes:

mask-clip: margin-box; (new!)

mask-clip: no-clip; (new!)

mask-clip: fill-box; (equivalent to content-box)

mask-clip: stroke-box; (equivalent to border-box)

mask-clip: view-box; (equivalent to border-box)



The implementation for margin-box and no-clip could use some

elaborating. There are two code changes:

1. CSSMaskPainter::MaskBoundingBox is used for property trees and now

uses a larger clip for margin-box and no-clip.

2. BackgroundImageGeometry::ComputeDestRectAdjustments now returns an

adjustment for margin-box and no-clip that is inflated. For margin-box,

this approach is important because we need to clip to the rounded

border radius created by the margin-box clip. No-clip follows the same

pattern for consistency.



Bug: 1418401

entry.title: CCA: Call LoadDocumentScanner in DocumentScannerServiceClient
entry.content:
In CCA, there are 2 clients using DocumentScannerServiceClient. One is

CameraAppHelperImpl, and the other is CameraAppDeviceImpl. CCA uses

CameraAppHelperImpl to check the document scanner status and uses

CameraAppDeviceImpl to do the ml method calls via mojo. Since

CheckDocumentModeReadiness will never be called by CameraAppDeviceImpl,

LoadDocumentScanner needs to be executed in constructor of

DocumentScannerServiceClient to support ML service like corner detection

in CCA.
